snippet: Tyson said its income rose to $166 million, or 44 cents a share, from $159 million, or 42 cents a share, a year earlier. Analysts on average were expecting 39 cents a share.
lead_paragraph: Tyson said its income rose to $166 million, or 44 cents a share, from $159 million, or 42 cents a share, a year earlier. Analysts on average were expecting 39 cents a share.

headline.main: Volume Sales Slip, but Tyson’s Earnings Exceed Analyst Estimates
